        <abstract> 
<p>Asks for copy of CD’s paper ["Ancient glaciers of Caernarvonshire", <hi rend="italic">Collected papers</hi> 1: 163–71]. Gathers that drift of Moel Tryfan is glacial.</p> 
            <p>Believes Glen Roy roads formed later than submergence of Scotland.</p>
            <p>Asks CD’s opinion concerning relative chronology of various glacial deposits, particularly a flint tool find in the Ouse River near Bedford.</p>
        </abstract>
